
### *Person 1: Playlist and Library Modules*
- *Frontend*:  
  - src/app/(routes)/playlist/  
  - src/app/(routes)/library/  
  - src/app/components/playlist/  
  - src/app/components/ui/Card.tsx (shared for playlist UI)  
  - src/app/hooks/usePlaylist.ts  

- *Backend*:  
  - src/app/api/playlists/route.ts  

---

### *Person 2: Home and Search Modules*
- *Frontend*:  
  - src/app/(routes)/home/  
  - src/app/(routes)/search/  
  - src/app/components/ui/Button.tsx and Input.tsx (shared for search UI)  
  - src/app/components/track/  
  - src/app/hooks/useAudioPlayer.ts  

- *Backend*:  
  - src/app/api/search/route.ts  
  - src/app/api/tracks/route.ts  

---

### *Shared Components & Contexts*
- *Person 1 and Person 2 can collaborate on*:  
  - src/app/components/layout/  
  - src/app/contexts/ (AudioPlayerContext and AuthContext)  
  - src/app/styles/  

---

### *Shared Utility Work*
Both should collaborate on:  
- src/app/lib/  
- src/app/types/  

This way, each person works on a feature that involves both frontend and backend, ensuring an equal and balanced workload.




